    <h2>Mademoiselle Caroline Rivie&#768;re</h2>
    <p>by <a href="painting1_large.jpg">Jean-Auguste-Dominique Ingres</a></p>
    <figure>
      <img src="painting1_medium.jpg" alt="girl in white dress" id="whiteDress">
    </figure>
    <p>The portrait of Mademoiselle Caroline Rivie&#768;re was painted in 1806 by the French Neoclassical artist Jean Auguste Dominique Ingres, and today hangs in the Louvre. It is the third of three portraits of the Rivie&#768;re family the artist painted that year.</p>
  <article>
  <article id="paintingDetails">
    <p>Date: <em>1806</em><br>
    Medium: <em>Oil on Canvas</em><br>
    Dimensions: <em>100 x 70 cm</em><br>
    Home: <em>Muse&#768;e du Louvre, Paris</em></p>
